===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|boot|lang=enm}}, {{term|bot|lang=enm}}, {{term|boet|lang=enm}}, {{term|boyt||boatlang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|bat|bāt|boat|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|baitaz|lang=gem-pro}}, {{recons|baitan||boat, small ship|lang=gem-pro}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{recons|bheid-||to break, split|lang=ine-pro}}. Cognate with {{etyl|non|-}} {{term|beit||boat|lang=non}}.

{{etyl|non|-}} {{term|bátr|bātr|lang=non}} (whence {{etyl|is|-}} {{term|bátur|lang=is}}, {{etyl|no|-}} {{term|båt|lang=no}}),  {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|boot|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|Boot|lang=de}}, and {{etyl|fr|-}} {{term|bateau|lang=fr}} are all ultimately borrowings from the {{ang}} word.

